nib.text:
Police are investigating after a man was fatally shot inside of an auto repair shop in St. Paul’s Payne-Phalen neighborhood.

St. Paul police responded to a report of a shooting on the 1300 block of Arcade Street around 3:40 p.m.

Arriving officers found a man with multiple gunshot wounds. He was pronounced deceased on the scene, police said. 

Police are investigating the circumstances surrounding the shooting. 

No arrests have been made. 

Anyone with information is asked to contact the police at 651-266-5650.
